# When No Error Occurs

```python
try:
    result = 10 / 2
except ZeroDivisionError:
    print("Error!")
else:
    print(f"Success: {result}")
```

`else` runs only if try succeeds!

slides.codeSnippet:
def try_divide(a, b):
    try:
        result = a / b
    except ZeroDivisionError:
        print(f"{a}/{b}: Error - division by zero")
    else:
        print(f"{a}/{b} = {result} (success!)")

try_divide(10, 2)
try_divide(10, 0)
try_divide(15, 5)
